In the summer of 2017, after the end of my junior year, I interned for six weeks at Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited (BSNL), an Indian state-owned Telecom Company. My training at BSNL started with classroom sessions to grasp the concepts of different instruments and technologies used in the telephone exchange. We were given lectures on all the technologies BSNL delved into and at the end of the week, we were instructed to present a presentation on the basis of our learning. After the classes were completed, we spent a week at different departments and assisted the administrators in the day to day operations. During my time with the customer care department, I helped the technicians in solving a data and records management query. In the third week, I was responsible for noting down readings coming from different landline telephone connection faults and then creating a digital record for the same. At the end of the fifth week, we were sent to various locations in the city to assess the signal strength of all the services provided by BSNL and construct a report and present our findings to our advisors.
